============================================================
  MATHEMATICS
============================================================

Theorem/Law:  Euler Polyhedron Formula
Branch:       Topology
Formula:      V - E + F = 2
Applications: Architecture, crystallography
Discoverer:   Leonhard Euler (1758)

Theorem/Law:  Pythagorean Theorem
Branch:       Geometry
Formula:      a² + b² = c²
Applications: Navigation, construction, computer graphics
Discoverer:   Pythagoras (500)

Theorem/Law:  Law of Large Numbers
Branch:       Probability
Formula:      Sample mean converges to expected value
Applications: Insurance, gambling, statistics
Discoverer:   Jacob Bernoulli (1713)

============================================================
  ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE & MACHINE LEARNING
============================================================

Concept:     Transformer
Category:    Architecture
Definition:  Attention-based model processing sequences in parallel
Year:        2017
Researchers: Vaswani et al.
Applications:LLMs, vision models, protein folding
Related:     GPT, BERT, attention mechanism

Concept:     Mixture of Experts
Category:    Architecture
Definition:  Sparse model activating different expert subsets per token
Year:        2017
Researchers: Shazeer et al.
Applications:Large LLMs (Mixtral, rumored GPT-4)
Related:     Sparse activation, routing, scaling efficiency

Concept:     Neural Scaling Laws
Category:    Theory
Definition:  Performance improves predictably with compute/data/parameters
Year:        2020
Researchers: Kaplan et al.
Applications:LLM development, compute planning
Related:     Chinchilla scaling, emergent abilities

============================================================
  ECONOMICS
============================================================

Concept:    Elasticity
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: Responsiveness of demand to price change
Formula:    PED = %dQd / %dP
Economist:  Alfred Marshall
Example:    Gasoline demand inelastic; luxury goods elastic

Concept:    Opportunity Cost
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: Value of next-best alternative foregone when choosing
Formula:    OC = forgone alternative value
Economist:  Bastiat
Example:    Studying means forgoing wages you could have earned working

Concept:    GDP
Category:   Macroeconomics
Definition: Total value of all goods and services produced in a country annually
Formula:    GDP = C + I + G + (X-M)
Economist:  Simon Kuznets
Example:    USA GDP 2023: $27.4 trillion; China: $17.9 trillion

============================================================
  DISEASES & MEDICINE
============================================================

Disease:     Malaria
Type:        Parasitic
Pathogen:    Plasmodium falciparum
Transmission:Mosquito bite
Symptoms:    Fever, chills, sweating cycles
Treatment:   Artemisinin combination therapy
Deaths/yr:   0.619M
Vaccine:     Yes (RTS,S approved 2021)
Discovered:  1880

Disease:     Diabetes Type 2
Type:        Metabolic
Pathogen:    Non-communicable
Transmission:Lifestyle
Symptoms:    Thirst, frequent urination, fatigue
Treatment:   Metformin, lifestyle, insulin
Deaths/yr:   1.5M
Vaccine:     No
Discovered:  1922

Disease:     Dengue
Type:        Viral
Pathogen:    Dengue virus
Transmission:Aedes mosquito
Symptoms:    Fever, severe joint pain, rash
Treatment:   Supportive care, fluids
Deaths/yr:   0.04M
Vaccine:     Yes (for previously infected)
Discovered:  1779

