Name:          Socrates
Lived:         470 - -399
Nationality:   Greek
Field:         Philosophy
Known For:     Socratic method
Contribution:  Father of Western philosophy; sentenced to death; documented by Plato
Quote:         "The only true wisdom is knowing you know nothing."

Name:          Abraham Lincoln
Lived:         1809 - 1865
Nationality:   American
Field:         Politics
Known For:     Emancipation Proclamation
Contribution:  16th US President; preserved Union; abolished slavery; Gettysburg Address
Quote:         "Government of the people, by the people, for the people."

Name:          Cleopatra VII
Lived:         69 - -30
Nationality:   Egyptian
Field:         Politics
Known For:     Last pharaoh of Egypt
Contribution:  Spoke 9 languages; allied with Caesar and Mark Antony; end of pharaonic era
Quote:         "I will not be triumphed over."

